  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Towards long-term Sustainable Change for Street Children (Kenya)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nyanza province in Kenya has twice as much HIV as the rest of the country. With so many adults sick and dying, many children from Nyanza have moved onto the streets to survive. Once on the street the kids lack food, health care, education and a safe place to sleep at night. They can be forced to do dangerous work and are often abused, raped and harassed. This project will reach out to children on the street, running a drop-in centre to provide essentials such as basic health care, a place to wash, counselling and education. It will provide somewhere to stay in the short term while the project tries to find families or guardians for them to move back in with. This project helps boys and girls to achieve lasting change so they can become independent adults.</narrative>
  </description>
